37
00:02:24.180 --> 00:02:28.400
If you have ever taken a cab ride, a taxi
ride, you understand regression.

38
00:02:28.400 --> 00:02:29.910
Here is how it works.

39
00:02:29.910 --> 00:02:34.459
The moment you sit in a cab ride, in a cab,
you see that there's a fixed amount there.

40
00:02:34.459 --> 00:02:35.940
It says $2.50.

41
00:02:35.940 --> 00:02:39.709
You, rather the cab, moves or you get off.

42
00:02:39.709 --> 00:02:43.319
This is what you owe to the driver the moment
you step into a cab.

43
00:02:43.319 --> 00:02:44.319
That's a constant.

44
00:02:44.319 --> 00:02:48.090
You have to pay that amount if you have stepped
into a cab.

45
00:02:48.090 --> 00:02:55.879
Then as it starts moving for every meter or
hundred meters the fare increases by certain

46
00:02:55.879 --> 00:02:56.879
amount.

47
00:02:56.879 --> 00:03:00.470
So there's a... there's a fraction, there's
a relationship between distance and the amount

48
00:03:00.470 --> 00:03:03.620
you would pay above and beyond that constant.

49
00:03:03.620 --> 00:03:08.000
And if you're not moving and you're stuck
in traffic, then every additional minute you

50
00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:09.500
have to pay more.

51
00:03:09.500 --> 00:03:12.980
So as the minutes increase, your fare increases.

52
00:03:12.980 --> 00:03:16.180
As the distance increases, your fare increases.

53
00:03:16.180 --> 00:03:21.120
And while all this is happening you've already
paid a base fare which is the constant.

54
00:03:21.120 --> 00:03:23.040
This is what regression is.

55
00:03:23.040 --> 00:03:28.480
Regression tells you what the base fare is
and what is the relationship between time

56
00:03:28.480 --> 00:03:32.400
and the fare you have paid, and the distance
you have traveled and the fare you've paid.

57
00:03:32.400 --> 00:03:37.370
Because in the absence of knowing those relationships,
and just knowing how much people traveled

58
00:03:37.370 --> 00:03:41.890
